      "text": "All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 6.1,
      "end": 11.16,
      "text": "For more information, or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 11.86,
      "end": 15.78,
      "text": "Recorded by Christine Doer, the known as Assa, Florida.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 17.52,
      "end": 21.18,
      "text": "Esaups fables, the oxen, and the axle trees.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 22.22,
      "end": 28.16,
      "text": "A pair of oxen were drawing a heavily loaded wagon along the highway, and as they tugged",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 28.16,
      "end": 32.46,
      "text": "and strained at the yoke, the axle trees creaked and groaned terribly.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 33.5,
      "end": 39.12,
      "text": "This was too much for the oxen, who turned round indignantly and said, Hello, you there!",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 40.2,
      "end": 43.16,
      "text": "Why do you make such a noise when we do all the work?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 44.52,
      "end": 46.98,
      "text": "They complain most, who suffer least.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 48.42,
      "end": 51.38,
      "text": "End of the oxen and the axle trees.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
